>> time required: 30 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/recipe-image-legacy-id-488488_11-2934f83.jpg?resize=768,574

Cook the @quinoa{200%g} in a large pan of boiling water for ~{10-15%min}s until tender, drain well, then set aside to cool.

Meanwhile, heat the @oil{1%tsp} in a small pan, then cook the shallot or @onion{0.75} for a few mins until softened. Add the @tarragon{2%tbsp}, stir well, then remove from the heat.

Stir the softened shallot and tarragon into the cooled quinoa along with the @lentils{207%g}, @cucumber{0.25}, @feta{100%g}, @spring onions{6}, @orange{1} zest and juice and @vinegar{1%tbsp}. Toss well together and chill until ready to serve.
